## Problem 1

Frequency analysis is a very important step in decypting a encypted message. Frequency analysis is based on the fact that some letters and words in the language appear more frequently in a text than others. For example, 'e', 't' and 'a' are some of the most common characters and 'the', 'of' etc. are the most common words in the english language. So, if we are decrypting a particular message and a letter 'X' has the most number of appearances we can guess that the letter might be 'e' or 'a', since those are among the most common. Then, we can replace all the occurences of 'X' in the text with an 'e'. Similarly, we can figure out other letters by trying until the words make sense. We can use similar logic for the words as well by looking at their length and occurences. This method is very effective if substitution cipher was used to encrypt the message.
